title: USWNT announce match in Honolulu against Trinidad and Tobago
text:
Updated Oct 15, 2015 at 9:09p ET 
CHICAGO -- 
The United States women's national team will play Trinidad and Tobago in Honolulu on Dec. 6 in the first international match played by the Americans in Hawaii. 
The Americans also will play Trinidad and Tobago on Dec. 10 at a site to be announced, the U.S. Soccer Federation said Thursday. 
The tour ends against China at the Superdome in New Orleans on Dec. 16. 
Two other December matches remain to be scheduled.
